		"rawItemType": 9,
		"itemType": "Review",
		"reviewID": 2343619,
		"rating": 5,
		"text": "Really good! I followed the recommendation of another user and used brown sugar in place of white. I also inculded a diced kiwi to tenderize the meat. I marinated for 6 hours and think next time I will leave it in overnight, just so the flavor has more time to soak in. But a truly great recipe! Yum!\n \nEDIT: I made this again and it marinated for two days, which was WAAAYYY too long! The soy sauce overpowered the other flavors. My recommendation is to marinate for no more than 24 hrs!",
		"dateLastModified": "2010-01-30T13:35:13.063",
