		"rawItemType": 9,
		"itemType": "Review",
		"reviewID": 272407,
		"rating": 5,
		"text": "I made a few changes to this recipe. First, I brushed the chicken with egg and rolled in breadcrumbs instead of flour. Second, I fried the chicken in butter for about 10 minutes until it was nicely browned, then I put it in the oven at 350 for another 20 minutes. Instead of simmering the chicken in the sauce, I whisked the cream,wine, bouillon and cornstarch in a bowl, then simmered it for about 10 min. alone, and spooned it over the chicken.\r\nIt turned out fantastic. My fiancee` said this was the best dish I ever made, and he's more of a beef man. Thank you!",
