		"rawItemType": 9,
		"itemType": "Review",
		"reviewID": 197383,
		"rating": 5,
		"text": "This really was easy and extremely adaptable.  I used catfish, but any white fish would work well - even a mixture of fish.  I increased the Old Bay Seasoning to 1 tsp +, and added the entire bottle of clam juice.  I also added 1 Tbls more than called for of flour, to make it a little thicker.  Next time I'll add the crumbled bacon into the soup, rather than use as a topping.  Top with parsley.  KEEPER!",
		"dateLastModified": "2003-05-02T10:49:32.263",
